title: Grateful Dead Live at Meadowlands Arena on 1987-04-06
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Dancin' In The Streets, Franklin's Tower, Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, When Push Comes To Shove, Jack Straw-> Deal

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, Cumberland Blues, Tons Of Steel, Saint Of Circumstance, Drums-> Jam-> Terrapin Station-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text:
Great show 87 seems underrated to me as a whole.

This show is just top notch from end to end. Like the Tons of Steel and When Push Comes to Shove, a bit off the beaten track.

It seems to me any time Cumberland Blues makes the playlist, the boys are having an on night.
